Performance Optimization: Enable Multi-threading (Non-blocking), use SIMD instructions where applicable, and ensure the code is optimized for 2 vCPU / 2GB RAM environment.
Static Linking: The final output must be a Single Static Binary with all symbols stripped (-s -w) to minimize startup time and RAM footprint on a Linux production server.
